scmi-hwmon registers the SCMI sensors successfully on Sky1 ACPI systems,
but then tries to bind each temperature sensor into an OF thermal zone.
ACPI does not provide those OF thermal-zone phandles, so the OF helper
returns -ENOTSUPP and the driver reports every temperature sensor as a
misconfigured thermal zone.

Only attempt OF thermal-zone registration when the SCMI device has an OF
node. This keeps the hwmon sensors available on ACPI and leaves ACPI
thermal zones to the ACPI thermal framework instead of reporting a false
DT misconfiguration.

---
 drivers/hwmon/scmi-hwmon.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/hwmon/scmi-hwmon.c b/drivers/hwmon/scmi-hwmon.c
--- a/drivers/hwmon/scmi-hwmon.c
+++ b/drivers/hwmon/scmi-hwmon.c
@@ -203,6 +203,9 @@ static int scmi_thermal_sensor_register(struct device *dev,
 	th_sensor->ph = ph;
 	th_sensor->info = sensor;
 
+	if (!dev->of_node)
+		return 0;
+
 	/*
 	 * Try to register a temperature sensor with the Thermal Framework:
 	 * skip sensors not defined as part of any thermal zone (-ENODEV) but
